who talked with me until dawn ♪

568
00:37:21,870 --> 00:37:25,470
♪ Let all the secrets be buried
in the wind and sand ♪

569
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:27,550
♪ Those moments of madness and hardship ♪

570
00:37:27,580 --> 00:37:30,300
♪ Were scattered by the wind
and turned into courage ♪

571
00:37:30,330 --> 00:37:32,780
♪ That eternal, quiet peace ♪

572
00:37:32,800 --> 00:37:34,630
♪ Gives me courage ♪

573
00:37:34,660 --> 00:37:36,600
♪ Consistent as ever ♪

574
00:37:36,620 --> 00:37:38,870
♪ Deeply rooted in my heart ♪

575
00:37:38,890 --> 00:37:41,520
♪ On the streets of Kashgar ♪

576
00:37:41,540 --> 00:37:43,400
♪ Holding hands ♪

577
00:37:43,420 --> 00:37:47,270
♪ Setting off just like that,
walking toward forever ♪

578
00:37:47,590 --> 00:37:49,990
♪ The uncertain, the swaying ♪

579
00:37:50,020 --> 00:37:52,020
♪ There is still time ♪

580
00:37:52,040 --> 00:37:55,940
♪ Steadying oneself, within reach ♪

581
00:37:56,420 --> 00:37:58,940
♪ At the entrance of the post house ♪

582
00:37:58,970 --> 00:38:00,660
♪ Holding hands once more ♪

583
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:05,050
♪ Dear friend,
the pomegranates are fully ripe ♪

584
00:38:14,580 --> 00:38:16,130
♪ Being a wife, being a mother ♪

585
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:18,680
♪ A woman surrounded by love ♪

586
00:38:18,890 --> 00:38:20,310
♪ I use love to illuminate ♪

587
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:22,930
♪ Warming my daughters ♪

588
00:38:23,220 --> 00:38:24,200
♪ Daughters ♪

589
00:38:24,220 --> 00:38:27,300
♪ We are the family
who loves you forever ♪

590
00:38:27,330 --> 00:38:31,540
♪ Home will always
keep its doors open for you ♪

591
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:33,080
But Dad,

592
00:38:33,100 --> 00:38:34,790
a girl's hands can mold clay,

593
00:38:34,820 --> 00:38:36,150
and they can also dance.

594
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:48,740
♪ Writing love and hope into songs ♪

595
00:38:48,770 --> 00:38:53,150
♪ Letting the whole world
sing along with me ♪

596
00:38:53,180 --> 00:38:57,250
♪ Holding my love for you
in the palms of my hands ♪

597
00:38:57,310 --> 00:39:01,110
♪ I cherish it carefully with you ♪

598
00:39:01,870 --> 00:39:06,030
♪ I treat you with sincere devotion,
always ♪

599
00:39:06,240 --> 00:39:10,270
♪ Without fearing the eyes of others ♪

600
00:39:10,610 --> 00:39:14,580
♪ Looking back at you
after enduring the wind and rain ♪

601
00:39:14,620 --> 00:39:19,060
♪ Love and courage make us shine ♪

602
00:39:19,520 --> 00:39:23,750
♪ La la la, I am here ♪

603
00:39:23,900 --> 00:39:27,550
♪ Spending my youth, I found you ♪

604
00:39:28,470 --> 00:39:32,890
♪ La, la, la, I am here ♪

605
00:39:32,920 --> 00:39:37,300
♪ Writing an eternal melody ♪

606
00:39:42,330 --> 00:39:43,850
On the way to set off again,

607
00:39:44,680 --> 00:39:45,950
I had a dream.

608
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:50,520
In the dream,
I heard the sound of the Satar again.

609
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:54,610
♪ The lover I long for ♪

610
00:39:54,650 --> 00:40:07,850
♪ May you live for a thousand years ♪

611
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:17,730
♪ May your tears hold no sorrow ♪

612
00:40:20,030 --> 00:40:23,790
♪ Since I saw you, my lover ♪

613
00:40:23,810 --> 00:40:31,980
♪ I have fallen into a pit of distress ♪

614
00:40:32,010 --> 00:40:35,480
♪ You set a fire in my heart ♪

615
00:40:43,300 --> 00:40:44,220
In the dream,

616
00:40:45,210 --> 00:40:46,980
just as a poet said,

617
00:40:49,300 --> 00:40:53,110
the people and things
that exist in memory,

618
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:55,820
the past and the future,

619
00:40:56,900 --> 00:40:58,500
the sound of music and dance,

620
00:40:59,350 --> 00:41:00,810
the streets and houses,

621
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:03,290
day and night,

622
00:41:03,910 --> 00:41:05,810
and reality and illusion—

623
00:41:06,590 --> 00:41:07,940
they all intermingle,

624
00:41:08,550 --> 00:41:09,880
blended like milk tea.

625
00:41:10,690 --> 00:41:12,620
The milk and tea become inseparable,

626
00:41:12,620 --> 00:41:15,620
leaving a lingering fragrance
that fills the senses.

627
00:42:22,430 --> 00:42:23,680
I once grew weary

628
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:27,010
and returned to my hometown

629
00:42:27,650 --> 00:42:28,420
for a nap.

630
00:42:30,010 --> 00:42:31,610
I had a vivid, colorful dream

631
00:42:34,630 --> 00:42:36,030
where I laughed out loud,

632
00:42:37,170 --> 00:42:38,230
cried my heart out,

633
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:41,940
sang at the top of my lungs,

634
00:42:42,590 --> 00:42:43,990
and danced with abandon.

635
00:42:46,520 --> 00:42:47,580
When I woke up,

636
00:42:49,040 --> 00:42:50,500
I set off again,

637
00:42:51,510 --> 00:42:52,550
no longer afraid.

638
00:43:02,490 --> 00:43:07,700
[Dedicated to us, as we set out once more]
